{
  "texts": [
    "However, Livni and Moran (2020) provide an example where the VC dimension is finite, yet the PAC-Bayes approach fails.",
    "This problem was solved recently by Grünwald et al. (2021) thanks to \"conditional PAC-Bayes bounds\".",
    "This is discussed below together with Mutual Information bounds.",
    "Similarly, generalization bounds for Support Vectors Machines are based on a quantity called the margin.",
    "This quantity can also appear in PAC-Bayes bounds (Langford and Shawe-Taylor, 2002; Herbrich and Graepel, 2002; Catoni, 2007; Biggs and Guedj, 2022)."
  ]
}